# Server Configuration
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development
HOST=0.0.0.0

# Stripe Keys (get these from https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here 
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_your_webhook_secret_here

# CORS - Frontend URL (for production, set to your actual frontend domain)
FRONTEND_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5500

# Supabase Configuration
   SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key_here
   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.[ref]:[password]@aws-0-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres

# Scanner configuration
SCANNER_PIN=your_4_digit_pin_here
SCANNER_ORIGIN=https://scanner.yourdomain.com


4. **Now create the actual `.env` file:**
   - Create a new file called `.env` (just `.env`, no other name)
   - Copy the same content as `.env.example`

**⚠️ IMPORTANT:** The `.env` file contains secrets and should NEVER be uploaded to GitHub or shared. We'll add it to `.gitignore` later.

